body.prompt:
Generate a fake conversation between a customer and an agent.
The agent should introduce themselves, their company and give the customer
their name. The agent should ask for the customer's name.
As part of the conversation, have the agent ask for two pieces of
personal information.  Spell out numbers. For example, 1000 should be
said as one zero zero zero, not one thousand. The conversation should be
at least 10 lines long and be complete. At the end
of the conversation, the agent should thank the customer for their time
and end the conversation. Return the conversation formatted 
like the following example:

{'conversation': 
    [
    {'speaker': 'Agent', 'message': 'xxxxx'}, 
    {'speaker': 'Customer', 'message': "xxxxx."}, 
    {'speaker': 'Agent', 'message': "xxxxxx"}
    ] 
}

body.speaker: Agent
body.message: Hello, thank you for contacting ABC Car Solutions. My name is Nathan Long. May I please have your name?

body.speaker: Agent
body.message: Nice to meet you, Ann. To assist you further, could you please provide me with your phone number?

body.speaker: Customer
body.message: Sure, my phone number is seven seven zero, two two one, four four eight nine.

body.speaker: Agent
body.message: Thank you. And may I also have your email address for our records?

body.speaker: Customer
body.message: Of course, my email is ann.flores@example.com.

body.speaker: Agent
body.message: Thank you for sharing that information, Ann. Is there anything else I can help you with today?

body.speaker: Customer
body.message: No, that's all for now. Thank you for your assistance.

body.speaker: Agent
body.message: You're welcome, Ann. Thank you for reaching out. Have a great day!
